result.execSummary:
The defendant Jina M. Pinc-Shaw was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Amphetamine/LSD/Psilocin, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(d).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
1) The defendant must provide DNA within 3 weeks from sentencing and pay the surcharge; the analysis may be expunged upon application to the Department of Justice. 
2) The Court waived all other court costs in this matter.
3) If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.
The defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety; no use or possession of any illegal drugs, paraphernalia, or controlled substances without a valid prescription.
The defendant shall maintain gainful employment or work towards obtaining a GED, HSED, or equivalent.

The defendant will be eligible to have this matter expunged upon successful and timely completion of probation if, at that time, all financial obligations associated with this case have been satisfied in full.

records.addlTxt:
9:14 AM Defendant Jina M. Pinc-Shaw appeared by video.  Attorney Daniel James Chapman appeared by video for Jina M. Pinc-Shaw.  Prosecuting attorney James Jay Rennicke Esq in court for the State of Wisconsin. Case is on for Plea/Sentencing Hearing.  Def waives all in person hearing KIV.  Agreement is recited by Court (from plq)- def pleading to amended Ct 1- amending possession of meth to possession of amphetamine, withheld sentence and 1 yr probation.  State makes formal motion to amend as stated; court grants.  Court asks def if they understand the agreement.  Def does.  Court reviews Def's constitutional rights.  Def understands that def is waiving those rights by entering into agreement today.  Court notes max poss. penalties differs from PLQ; def understands.  Court asks Def if they understand Court is not bound by agreement, and could order maximum penalties.  Def understands.  Court asks for plea. Def enters a plea of Guilty.  Court finds def is making plea knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily.  Court finds a factual basis to accept the plea.  Court finds defendant guilty of amended Count 1 and orders a JOC; remaining counts are DRI.  DA asks Court to accept agreement.  Defense attorney asks Court to accept agreement, asks for expunction eligibility.  Def does not make a statement to the Court.  State does not object to finding def eligible for expunction.  Discussion of where probation must be served.  
Court orders:
1 year probation; 4 months jail, imposed/stayed
Conditions: 
The defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety. No use or possession of any illegal drugs, paraphernalia, or controlled substances without a valid prescription. Gainful employment or work towards GED, HSED, or equivalent.  $200 DNA only.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.  Eligible for expungement if paid in full at successful discharge from probation.
Appeal rights provided.  DNA to be provided to the Sheriff's Department. Def to call and arrange probation today by 4pm.  Def to provide DNA to BCSD within three weeks.  13 days jail credit if revoked.
